      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion, my goblin-infused guidance may have led us astray. Let's get straight to the point then. From Heathrow (LHR) to Singapore (SIN), you have a few airlines to choose from. British Airways, Emirates, Qatar Airways, and Singapore Airlines are some of the main carriers that operate this route. \n\nTo prioritize and avoid wasting hours in lines, here are a few tips:\n\n1. Check the flight status board for the next available departures. This will give you an idea of the flight times and help you prioritize which flights to book first.\n2. Look for flights that have a shorter layover time. This will allow you to spend less time waiting and more time enjoying your journey.\n3. Consider booking flights that have a higher chance of being on time. This can be determined by looking at the flight history of each airline and flight number.\n4. If possible, book flights that have a shorter walking distance between terminals. This will save you time and energy.\n\nI hope this helps you find the best flight for your journey. Safe travels!",
